57:26.359 --> 57:30.738
but anyway those are importantfigures from history.

57:30.780 --> 57:35.201
That's exactly my point.

57:35.243 --> 57:37.036
So are you.

57:41.708 --> 57:44.878
Um... we should finishgetting ready.

57:44.919 --> 57:46.921
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

57:59.684 --> 58:00.935
Welcome, Mr. Niven.

58:00.977 --> 58:03.021
Thank you for your interestin buying Wycliff House.

58:03.062 --> 58:03.938
My pleasure.

58:04.189 --> 58:06.649
Hannah's told me great thingsabout you both.

58:06.691 --> 58:08.943
Well, we have a visionto present to you today,

58:08.985 --> 58:10.820
and though it might not be quitewhat you expected

58:10.862 --> 58:13.865
we believe it's an evenbetter opportunity

58:13.907 --> 58:16.117
than just a golf course.

58:16.159 --> 58:18.244
So, without further ado...

58:21.456 --> 58:26.127
Imagine a resort with all theamenities of a five-star hotel.

58:26.169 --> 58:28.838
Golf, a spa, luxuryaccommodations...

58:28.880 --> 58:33.593
and with all the historyof a world-class museum.

58:33.635 --> 58:35.970
And as the guests wanderthrough the estate...

58:36.012 --> 58:37.931
They will stroll back in time

58:37.972 --> 58:42.518
and imagine themselvesas Vanderbilts or Morgans,

58:42.560 --> 58:46.564
living the lives of gentlemenor debutants.

58:46.564 --> 58:51.152
They will walk amid livinghistory and experience life

58:51.194 --> 58:53.655
in the Gilded Age first-hand.

58:53.696 --> 58:56.699
And then afterwards they mightenjoy a round of golf

58:56.741 --> 58:59.869
or a cocktail by the fire.

58:59.911 --> 59:02.038
Please follow me.

59:07.585 --> 59:10.505
And our rose garden providesthe ideal location

59:10.547 --> 59:12.423
for weddings and events.

59:12.465 --> 59:15.510
While paying homage tothe estate's historic character.

59:15.552 --> 59:17.929
All with five-star diningand accommodations.

59:17.929 --> 59:20.515
All our plans are herein our proposal

59:20.556 --> 59:23.935
and uh, here's our vision ofhow the house

59:23.977 --> 59:26.020
can be renovatedand preserved.

59:26.062 --> 59:29.148
A fusion of historic splendorand modern luxury

59:29.190 --> 59:32.402
while keeping this magnificentestate intact.

59:32.443 --> 59:34.320
All while delivering one ofthe finest golf courses

59:34.362 --> 59:36.698
in New England.

59:36.739 --> 59:39.117
Please.

59:39.158 --> 59:41.160
Thank you.

59:41.202 --> 59:43.037
What is going on?

59:43.079 --> 59:44.789
This is not what we discussed.

59:44.831 --> 59:45.665
It's fine.

59:45.707 --> 59:46.583
Everything is gonnabe fine.

59:46.791 --> 59:48.167
You'll see. Just waituntil tomorrow.

59:48.209 --> 59:52.130
And you'll still getyour finder's fee, I promise.

59:52.130 --> 59:55.341
Oh I hope you knowwhat you're doing.

59:59.679 --> 01:00:00.847
More and more people

01:00:00.888 --> 01:00:02.890
are visiting the townof Newton lately,

01:00:02.932 --> 01:00:07.145
making this a unique businessopportunity for you.

01:00:07.186 --> 01:00:09.939
But it's more than that.

01:00:09.981 --> 01:00:12.775
I spent all my summers hereas a girl

01:00:12.817 --> 01:00:19.073
and it was the happiest timeof my life.

01:00:19.115 --> 01:00:21.576
I'd like others to experiencethat, too.

01:00:21.617 --> 01:00:24.871
Which is why I'd like to makethis a condition of the sale.

01:00:25.663 --> 01:00:27.165
And on that note,let me show you

01:00:27.165 --> 01:00:29.667
where you could plan to putthe back nine.

01:00:29.709 --> 01:00:31.794
And at our ball tonightyou'll get a glimpse of

01:00:31.836 --> 01:00:35.048
what life was like herein the Gilded Age.

01:00:35.089 --> 01:00:37.133
Looking forward to it.

01:00:52.774 --> 01:00:56.694
[phone rings]

01:00:56.694 --> 01:00:58.154
I hate to interrupt your fairytale

01:00:58.196 --> 01:00:59.197
but I'm trying to round up

01:00:59.447 --> 01:01:01.157
all of the trustees foryour conference call later

01:01:01.199 --> 01:01:02.992
but everyone's in differenttime zones.

01:01:03.034 --> 01:01:06.829
One's traveling in Dubai,another in Singapore...

01:01:06.871 --> 01:01:08.164
I'll keep you posted.

01:01:08.206 --> 01:01:09.165
Great.

01:01:09.415 --> 01:01:11.626
I'm just juggling a few thingshere but I'll be ready.

01:01:11.668 --> 01:01:14.170
(Duncan): Lucy, the caterers are here I need your help!

01:01:14.212 --> 01:01:16.714
Sounds like a gentleman caller awaits.

01:01:16.714 --> 01:01:18.132
I have to get readyfor the ball.

01:01:18.174 --> 01:01:20.635
Have fun, and I'll give youone hour heads up

01:01:20.677 --> 01:01:22.387
before your call sothat you can get settled.

01:01:22.428 --> 01:01:23.179
Perfect.

01:01:23.221 --> 01:01:24.180
Thanks, Josephine.

01:01:24.222 --> 01:01:25.431
Bye.

01:01:33.106 --> 01:01:42.323
[classical music plays]♪

01:01:45.702 --> 01:01:46.911
I would have invitedyou by sending a letter

01:01:46.911 --> 01:01:49.330
but I was worriedthat it would take too...

01:01:58.881 --> 01:01:59.924
You look amazing.

01:01:59.966 --> 01:02:02.552
You look pretty nice yourself.

01:02:02.593 --> 01:02:04.929
Thanks. I um, I borrowedthis from Randall.

01:02:04.929 --> 01:02:07.682
I'm feeling a littleoverdressed.

01:02:07.724 --> 01:02:11.269
Don't. It suits you.

01:02:15.273 --> 01:02:17.024
Shall we?

01:02:19.944 --> 01:02:22.864
May I introduce our hostsfor the evening,

01:02:22.905 --> 01:02:24.991
Lucy and Duncan ofWycliff House.

01:02:25.032 --> 01:02:31.456
[applause]

01:02:31.456 --> 01:02:34.125
Lucy, aren't you a vision?

01:02:34.167 --> 01:02:36.169
Oh, your aunt would be so happy

01:02:36.210 --> 01:02:38.296
there's dancing inthe ballroom again.

01:02:38.337 --> 01:02:39.964
Thank you, Eleanor.

01:02:39.964 --> 01:02:42.842
You know, I would take thisover some stuffy donor's

01:02:42.884 --> 01:02:46.804
cocktail party any day.

01:02:46.846 --> 01:02:48.181
I don't see Niven.

01:02:48.222 --> 01:02:50.057
Lucy, it's time.

01:02:50.099 --> 01:02:53.853
Your aunt always openedthe gala with a few words.

01:03:00.985 --> 01:03:03.529
Hey, thanks for coming.

01:03:05.072 --> 01:03:06.407
Hey.

01:03:14.999 --> 01:03:17.335
Thank you allfor coming tonight.

01:03:17.335 --> 01:03:19.754
Before our evening beginsI want to share with you

01:03:19.795 --> 01:03:23.132
something my Aunt Gracealways told me.

01:03:23.174 --> 01:03:26.969
How her grandfather-in-law,Henry Wycliff,

01:03:27.011 --> 01:03:32.600
felt that this housewas for everyone.

01:03:32.642 --> 01:03:35.978
Here the gardenermight find himself at dinner

01:03:36.020 --> 01:03:41.359
eating peach pie next toPresident Grover Cleveland.

01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:44.820
Henry opened his doorsto all

01:03:44.862 --> 01:03:48.074
and my Aunt Grace would beso happy to know

01:03:48.115 --> 01:03:53.204
that we're keepingthat spirit alive tonight.

01:03:53.204 --> 01:03:56.457
I'm not sure I can followin my Aunt Grace's footsteps

01:03:56.499 --> 01:04:01.212
but I will try my best.

01:04:01.254 --> 01:04:07.301
And on that note, letthe first dance begin.

01:04:07.343 --> 01:04:12.056
[applause]

01:04:12.056 --> 01:04:14.016
You ready?

01:04:14.058 --> 01:04:16.269
Ready as I'll ever be.

01:04:26.070 --> 01:04:27.113
You ok?

