01:09:38.506 --> 01:09:40.801
Not throw me overboard.

01:09:40.843 --> 01:09:42.386
Look, you said it yourself.

01:09:42.428 --> 01:09:44.889
It was fine to tear down the estate if that's what it took

01:09:44.889 --> 01:09:45.890
to make the sale.

01:09:46.180 --> 01:09:50.603
Yes, yes, I said it was fineto tear down the estate,

01:09:50.644 --> 01:09:52.729
but now I think we havea better option.

01:09:52.770 --> 01:09:55.566
Which Niven doesn't want.

01:09:55.608 --> 01:09:57.234
Ok, look. We have about a dayto sell Niven

01:09:57.276 --> 01:09:58.444
on the plan that he expected.

01:09:58.736 --> 01:10:02.698
I suggest that you come up withsomething to change his mind.

01:10:02.740 --> 01:10:05.201
[door slams]

01:10:05.242 --> 01:10:08.245
Just give me a second.

01:10:10.247 --> 01:10:11.749
Lucy!

01:10:16.420 --> 01:10:21.091
So you're still fine tearingdown the entire place?

01:10:21.091 --> 01:10:25.512
Were you- were you just snoopingon me?

01:10:25.554 --> 01:10:29.642
Echo-y halls, remember?

01:10:29.683 --> 01:10:33.729
Yeah, I uh- I promised Hannahthat I'd try to convince you

01:10:33.771 --> 01:10:37.733
to sell to Niven.

01:10:37.775 --> 01:10:41.570
To level the estatefor a golf course.

01:10:41.612 --> 01:10:45.491
Well, it just- it felt like themost practical plan at the time-

01:10:45.532 --> 01:10:46.533
Practical.

01:10:46.825 --> 01:10:49.536
Again, more proof we werenever right for each other.

01:10:49.578 --> 01:10:53.707
I don't know why I'mso surprised, Duncan.

01:10:53.749 --> 01:10:56.460
You always do what's rightfor you.

01:10:59.255 --> 01:11:02.383
Wait, that's not... Lucy...

01:11:02.424 --> 01:11:03.968
Lucy.

01:11:16.563 --> 01:11:17.439
[phone alert]

01:11:19.650 --> 01:11:21.527
There might be hope for us yet,Duncan.

01:11:21.568 --> 01:11:22.653
I'm not so sure about that.

01:11:22.987 --> 01:11:25.197
Lucy just texted, she's willingto give us carte blanche

01:11:25.239 --> 01:11:26.740
to do whatever we wantwith the estate.

01:11:26.782 --> 01:11:27.533
Just now?

01:11:27.741 --> 01:11:29.410
This improvesour hand immensely.

01:11:29.451 --> 01:11:31.829
It should be easy to finda buyer now.

01:11:31.829 --> 01:11:33.372
Who wants to tear downthe estate.

01:11:33.414 --> 01:11:38.377
Duncan, you said that you wantedto be free of this place.

01:11:38.419 --> 01:11:40.212
This is your chance.

01:11:40.254 --> 01:11:42.756
A chance to move onto something new.

01:11:42.798 --> 01:11:45.009
You'll have enough to set upyour own firm in Boston

01:11:45.009 --> 01:11:47.886
just like you hoped.

01:11:47.928 --> 01:11:50.723
It's time to thinkabout the future.

01:11:57.479 --> 01:12:03.610
[phone rings]

01:12:09.450 --> 01:12:14.246
Isabelle. I am so sorryabout last night.

01:12:14.288 --> 01:12:17.207
Why would you need to apologize?

01:12:17.207 --> 01:12:20.461
Well, after the wholeteleconference fiasco.

01:12:20.502 --> 01:12:22.838
Yes, well, Lucy, your spreadsheets spoke

01:12:22.880 --> 01:12:23.714
for themselves.

01:12:23.964 --> 01:12:25.382
So I hope you're gettinga chance to relax

01:12:25.424 --> 01:12:26.508
because when you get back

01:12:26.550 --> 01:12:29.511
you'll have somebig shoes to step into.

01:12:29.553 --> 01:12:30.888
Which shoes?

01:12:30.888 --> 01:12:32.556
Specifically mine.

01:12:32.556 --> 01:12:35.476
The trustees votedto approve you.

01:12:35.517 --> 01:12:36.727
You're kidding?

01:12:36.769 --> 01:12:39.938
There'll be a boost in salary, of course.

01:12:39.980 --> 01:12:40.856
That's wonderful.

01:12:41.065 --> 01:12:42.566
Yes, and we'll discuss itall on Monday

01:12:42.608 --> 01:12:45.277
when you're back in London.

01:12:45.319 --> 01:12:47.404
You need an answer now?

01:12:47.446 --> 01:12:50.866
Lucy, perhaps youdon't understand.

01:12:50.908 --> 01:12:51.742
The trustees approved you.

01:12:51.784 --> 01:12:53.660
You got the job you wanted.

01:12:53.702 --> 01:12:56.872
The one a million peoplewould kill for.

01:12:56.914 --> 01:12:58.207
Yes.

01:12:58.248 --> 01:13:02.377
No, um... of course,I'm as happy as...

01:13:02.419 --> 01:13:05.839
As Alexander when he conqueredEgypt in 332 B.C.?

01:13:05.881 --> 01:13:07.382
Yes.

01:13:07.424 --> 01:13:11.261
No, exactly.

01:13:11.303 --> 01:13:14.848
I gladly accept the job,Isabelle.

01:13:14.890 --> 01:13:15.891
Thank you.

01:13:16.183 --> 01:13:18.852
And I will see you tomorrowwhen I fly back to London.

01:13:18.894 --> 01:13:20.187
Good.

01:13:20.229 --> 01:13:22.731
Bye-bye.

01:13:35.953 --> 01:13:39.373
Oh, Lucy. You're up early.

01:13:39.414 --> 01:13:43.043
I was wondering if you couldgive me a ride to the airport?

01:13:43.085 --> 01:13:47.422
Oh. Of course.

01:13:47.464 --> 01:13:51.844
I didn't know you were goingback to England so soon.

01:13:51.885 --> 01:13:53.846
Honestly, neither did I.

01:13:55.556 --> 01:14:00.769
Well, um, just let me finish uphere and I'll get my coat

01:14:00.811 --> 01:14:02.896
and I'll be right with you.

01:14:02.938 --> 01:14:04.773
Ok.

01:14:14.449 --> 01:14:17.119
Marcus, we got a problem.

01:14:28.839 --> 01:14:30.883
I'm really gonna missthis place.

01:14:30.924 --> 01:14:34.511
And you'll be missedin Newton.

01:14:34.553 --> 01:14:36.638
So how long is your flight back?

01:14:36.680 --> 01:14:40.017
Door to doorabout 10 hours but uh,

01:14:40.058 --> 01:14:42.519
I brought some reading.

01:14:42.561 --> 01:14:44.730
Aunt Grace's diary.

01:14:44.771 --> 01:14:47.357
I thought I'd take it backwith me as a keepsake.

01:14:47.399 --> 01:14:49.943
I think Grace would haveliked that.

01:14:57.284 --> 01:14:59.536
Goodbye, Lucy.

01:14:59.578 --> 01:15:01.705
Goodbye.

01:15:25.812 --> 01:15:27.523
Something wrong, Duncan?

01:15:27.564 --> 01:15:29.608
You usually wolf downmy Monte Cristo sandwich

01:15:29.650 --> 01:15:31.693
in two seconds flat.

01:15:31.735 --> 01:15:36.240
Niven flies off in about an hourand I need to finish this pitch.

01:15:36.240 --> 01:15:37.533
You know, Eleanor just called

01:15:37.574 --> 01:15:39.910
to tell me Lucy leftfor the airport.

01:15:42.287 --> 01:15:44.081
She left?

01:15:51.755 --> 01:15:53.674
Headstrong as always.

01:15:53.715 --> 01:15:56.176
Who's the headstrong one here?

01:15:56.218 --> 01:15:57.427
And proud, as well.

01:15:57.469 --> 01:15:59.429
You think I'm being proud?

01:15:59.429 --> 01:16:01.598
She won't even give me a chanceto explain.

01:16:01.598 --> 01:16:03.767
You let her go once.

01:16:03.767 --> 01:16:05.894
Are you gonna let her slipthrough your fingers again?

01:16:05.936 --> 01:16:06.895
What choice do I have?

01:16:06.937 --> 01:16:10.023
Go stop her.

01:16:10.065 --> 01:16:13.569
I don't think she wantsto see me right now.

01:16:13.610 --> 01:16:19.950
You know, your dad and Iwere good friends.

01:16:19.992 --> 01:16:24.955
If he was here I'm pretty surewhat he'd say.

01:16:24.997 --> 01:16:26.832
What's that?

01:16:26.873 --> 01:16:28.792
Being caretaker of the estate

01:16:28.834 --> 01:16:32.838
was more than justchanging lightbulbs.

01:16:32.879 --> 01:16:37.634
Your dad thought he was acaretaker of something precious.

01:16:37.676 --> 01:16:40.220
He knew some thingswere worth saving.

01:16:56.653 --> 01:16:59.865
Randall? I've got a job for you.

01:17:27.267 --> 01:17:31.021
Lucy, Lucy, hey wait!

01:17:31.063 --> 01:17:33.023
Duncan,what're you doing here?

01:17:33.065 --> 01:17:34.691
I need to talk to you.

01:17:34.691 --> 01:17:36.026
I couldn't let you go backto London again

01:17:36.068 --> 01:17:39.738
without you understanding.

01:17:39.780 --> 01:17:44.368
I never wanted to let you gothat last summer.

01:17:44.409 --> 01:17:46.036
I know.

01:17:46.036 --> 01:17:49.790
I... I read Aunt Grace's journal

01:17:49.831 --> 01:17:54.878
and her descriptions of howyou waited for me

01:17:54.878 --> 01:17:56.463
every summer before I arrived

01:17:56.505 --> 01:18:02.219
and how sad you wereevery summer after I left.

01:18:02.260 --> 01:18:04.846
I need you to give meone more chance.

01:18:04.888 --> 01:18:06.139
A chance for what?

01:18:06.181 --> 01:18:08.809
I've been working on thisproposal for Niven.

01:18:08.850 --> 01:18:11.019
It's a long shot but I thinkhe might just go for it.

01:18:11.061 --> 01:18:15.273
Would you just postponeyour flight for one more day?

01:18:15.315 --> 01:18:16.858
I don't know, Duncan.

01:18:16.900 --> 01:18:20.862
You were right, it does seema little impractical.

01:18:25.242 --> 01:18:27.202
Letting you go was the mostpractical decision

01:18:27.244 --> 01:18:30.497
that I have ever made.

01:18:30.539 --> 01:18:34.751
It's also the worst decisionof my entire life.

01:18:34.751 --> 01:18:38.755
Now I'm asking youto trust me.

01:18:38.797 --> 01:18:40.048
Please.

01:18:46.930 --> 01:18:49.725
What did you have in mind?

01:18:49.766 --> 01:18:52.018
I will tell you all about iton the way back.

01:18:52.060 --> 01:18:56.064
But right now I believe we havea billionaire to catch.

01:18:56.106 --> 01:18:57.816
Ok.

01:19:07.284 --> 01:19:08.118
Right, no, I understand

01:19:08.326 --> 01:19:11.121
Mr. Niven's timeis incredibly limited.

01:19:11.163 --> 01:19:14.249
Ok. We will certainly try.

01:19:14.291 --> 01:19:15.250
Thank you so much.

01:19:15.292 --> 01:19:16.460
Yeah.

01:19:16.501 --> 01:19:17.544
Bye-bye.

01:19:17.836 --> 01:19:21.173
Ok, so Niven is flying outto Aspen to meet his grandkids

01:19:21.214 --> 01:19:23.008
but his assistant said thatwe might be able to catch him

01:19:23.049 --> 01:19:25.302
before he checks out of hishotel and heads to the airport

01:19:25.302 --> 01:19:27.345
but he's leaving very soon.

01:19:29.806 --> 01:19:31.391
You my ride?

01:19:34.394 --> 01:19:37.189
Yes sir. That I am.

01:19:38.482 --> 01:19:40.233
(Lucy): Shoot, it's the festival. I forgot.

01:19:40.275 --> 01:19:45.030
(Duncan): It's the last day. We'll have to go on foot.

01:19:45.071 --> 01:19:46.907
(Lucy): Alright.

01:19:51.411 --> 01:19:53.455
Oh, wow. We gotta hurry.

01:19:53.497 --> 01:19:55.290
Ok, come on. Follow me.

01:19:55.999 --> 01:19:56.416
Excuse me.

01:19:56.458 --> 01:19:57.167
Excuse us.

01:19:57.209 --> 01:19:58.543
Excuse me.

01:20:00.921 --> 01:20:02.088
Oh, this is impossible.

01:20:02.130 --> 01:20:02.589
Sorry.

01:20:02.631 --> 01:20:03.507
Sorry.

01:20:03.840 --> 01:20:05.926
Listen, young man, I've gota plane waiting for me.

01:20:07.886 --> 01:20:09.846
I just can't figure it out.

01:20:09.888 --> 01:20:12.182
It's never happened before.

01:20:12.182 --> 01:20:13.975
I probably just floodedthe engine.

01:20:14.017 --> 01:20:16.061
I'll have it up and runningin no time.

01:20:20.023 --> 01:20:22.234
Hey, Duncan, hold up.Come here.

01:20:27.864 --> 01:20:29.157
How much?

01:20:36.248 --> 01:20:37.582
Ah, look at that.

01:20:37.624 --> 01:20:39.709
Ready to go.

01:20:39.709 --> 01:20:41.378
Unless, do you wannagrab a bite?

01:20:41.378 --> 01:20:42.546
I know a greatrestaurant nearby.

01:20:42.546 --> 01:20:45.006
Just drive, please.

01:20:45.048 --> 01:20:46.091
Right.

01:20:48.552 --> 01:20:49.553
Mr. Niven!

01:20:50.178 --> 01:20:52.430
Do you have just a minuteor two?

01:20:59.145 --> 01:21:02.482
Look, I appreciate your effortsbut you need to understand that

01:21:02.524 --> 01:21:05.068
I'm not in the habit ofreconsidering an offer

01:21:05.110 --> 01:21:06.194
I've already turned down.

01:21:06.486 --> 01:21:10.282
Right, but we're not talkingabout a purchase anymore,

01:21:10.323 --> 01:21:13.827
we're talking about a smallseed investment.

01:21:13.868 --> 01:21:16.496
Less risk for you,much more return.

01:21:16.538 --> 01:21:17.998
Now, you told us that your heartsaid yes

01:21:18.039 --> 01:21:20.000
but the numbers said no,right?

01:21:20.041 --> 01:21:23.378
Well, now I think you'll findthe numbers say yes.

01:21:23.420 --> 01:21:25.297
I was able to re-worksome of the renovation costs

01:21:25.338 --> 01:21:27.841
and save us some money soafter an initial investment

01:21:27.882 --> 01:21:32.262
we can renovate as we gofunded solely by profits.

01:21:32.262 --> 01:21:34.055
It's all in here.

01:21:37.142 --> 01:21:39.811
I'll look at it on the plane.

01:21:39.853 --> 01:21:41.479
But even assuming your numbersadd up why would

01:21:41.521 --> 01:21:44.316
I want to invest ina historical resort?

01:21:44.357 --> 01:21:46.902
For a reason you can'tput a price on.

01:21:46.943 --> 01:21:48.778
Preserving your legacy.

01:21:48.820 --> 01:21:51.448
You're a grandfather, right?

01:21:51.448 --> 01:21:53.116
Ok, well how do you wantyour grandkids

01:21:53.158 --> 01:21:54.993
to remember their grandpa?

01:21:55.035 --> 01:21:57.245
As the generous man whoput them through college.

01:21:57.287 --> 01:21:58.663
[laughs]

01:21:58.705 --> 01:22:01.875
My aunt used to tell me storiesabout another generous man.

01:22:01.917 --> 01:22:04.294
A railroad baron namedHenry Wycliff

01:22:04.336 --> 01:22:05.921
who was a very wealthy man

01:22:05.962 --> 01:22:07.964
but he also wanted everyonearound him

01:22:08.006 --> 01:22:09.799
to live rich lives, too.

01:22:09.841 --> 01:22:13.803
He built this whole town.Its parks, its library.

01:22:13.845 --> 01:22:16.931
His spirit is everywhere here.

01:22:16.973 --> 01:22:20.143
You can see for yourself.It's all in here.

01:22:20.185 --> 01:22:21.978
People still rememberhis generosity

01:22:22.020 --> 01:22:26.274
and if you have the visionto help preserve his legacy

01:22:26.316 --> 01:22:29.819
then maybe in 100 yearsfrom now

01:22:29.861 --> 01:22:34.532
people will be remembering youwith the same fondness.

01:22:34.574 --> 01:22:37.994
That's the great thingabout history.

01:22:38.036 --> 01:22:40.288
It lasts forever.

01:22:43.333 --> 01:22:45.168
I'll be in touch.

01:22:49.631 --> 01:22:51.466
Let's go.

01:23:17.158 --> 01:23:20.286
I just got off the phonewith Hannah.

01:23:20.328 --> 01:23:23.998
I think you may havejust sold him on it.

01:23:24.040 --> 01:23:28.336
Well, convincing donorswas my job.

01:23:28.378 --> 01:23:30.505
Was?

01:23:30.547 --> 01:23:32.298
I realized something.

01:23:32.340 --> 01:23:34.384
My future isn't in some office

01:23:34.426 --> 01:23:36.594
five stories abovethe exhibits I love

01:23:36.636 --> 01:23:40.432
doing spreadsheets.

01:23:40.473 --> 01:23:43.518
My future is here.

01:23:43.560 --> 01:23:47.021
So you'll stay?

01:23:47.063 --> 01:23:49.232
This is where I belong.

01:23:49.232 --> 01:23:54.696
My home is hereand so is my heart.

01:24:49.334 --> 01:24:51.669
Great, thank you.

01:24:56.466 --> 01:24:57.717
[sighs]

01:24:57.759 --> 01:24:59.219
Not bad.

01:24:59.260 --> 01:25:02.138
Not bad at all.

01:25:02.138 --> 01:25:04.682
So how does it feel to haveyour architectural office

01:25:04.724 --> 01:25:07.227
in your own house?

01:25:07.268 --> 01:25:08.478
My house?

01:25:08.520 --> 01:25:10.563
Wait a second,I thought this was your house.

01:25:10.605 --> 01:25:14.359
[laughs]

01:25:14.400 --> 01:25:16.361
It's our house.

01:25:16.778 --> 01:25:18.863
It's our house.
